h4. Actual behavior:
When you have an URL that contains special characters as {{[}} or spaces, JIRA can't create a Web Link. It fails with the following error:

{noformat}
Invalid 'URL'. Make sure you include the full URL (e.g. http://www.google.com).
{noformat}

h4. Steps to Reproduce:

- Open an issue and click on _More_ and then in _Link_. Choose Web Link.
- In the URL, paste: {noformat}https://my.url.com/site/bla/INTERNAL Projects/Default Documentation /[Important] File.doc{noformat}
- The error above will be displayed when you try to create the link.

h4. Expected behavior:

JIRA should create the Web Link and if necessary, act as the web browser and convert the url from:
{noformat}
https://my.url.com/site/bla/INTERNAL Projects/Default Documentation /[Important] File.doc
{noformat}
To:
{noformat}
https://my.url.com/site/bla/INTERNAL%20Projects/Default%20Documentation%20/%5BImportant%5D%20File.doc
{noformat}

h4. Workaround:

Currently, you can paste the URL on your browser and copy the converted version. Then you can paste it in JIRA.

