I might be wrong but I believe there is no way to determine the type/class for the value object of a CustomField. This means that if you want to assign a value to the CustomField, you need to try to assign it and catch a ClassCastException exception, but there is no way to determine in advance if this assignment will succeed, before trying to assign the value to CustomField.

That being said, it might be a good idea to implement a method named something like getValueType() or getValueClass() which would allow us to do something like this:

CustomField cf = ... ; // our custom field
Object newValue = ... ; // provided new Value for the CustomField
if (cf.getValueType().equals(newValue.getClass())
// now we know we could assign the value to the custom field without an exception

